Sentencas: In this work, an alternative anode material, consisting of perovskite-type manganese doped lanthanum aluminate (La1.5Al0.33Mn0.17O3), was proposed and implemented.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst

Sentencas: The solid oxide fuel cell anode was produced by the wet impregnation of nanoparticles into a macroporous electrolyte-based scaffold material.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst

Sentencas: The produced cell was characterized by X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy, from which the morphology of the scaffold, the particle size distribution, and porosity were extensively performed and discussed.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst

Sentencas: Electrochemical and electrocatalytic tests were accounted by recording i-V plots with hydrogen or methane as fuels, and by measuring methane conversion rates and C-2 hydrocarbons selectivity.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst

Sentencas: The particle size distribution was confirmed to be submicrometric with the presence of nanoparticles.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst

Sentencas: High levels of porosity (30-35%) were achieved at the scaffold and the cells were able to operate with hydrogen and methane as fuels delivering a power density of around 150 mW.cm(-2) and yielding 30-70% C-2 hydrocarbons selectivity, depending on operational conditions.
Titulo: Multifunctional macroporous solid oxide fuel cell anode with active nanosized ceramic electrocatalyst
